      "content": "i see what u mean about the structure, but it feels like you're penalizing them more for their dialect/slang than for their actual ability to do the job. \n\nif we consider that many successful, highly intelligent people use more casual or dialect-specific language in everyday life, isn't it a bit of a stretch to say they aren't \"capable\" just because they don't use \"Standard American English\"? like, if a candidate is incredibly smart and great with people but just speaks more colloquially, should they really be disqualified from a professional role? wouldn't that be a bit biased?",
